(Main Lesson) Tj
T*
(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Programming teaches students how to give computers step-by-step instructions to solve) Tj
T*
(problems. In a textbook lesson, the first goal is to make the computing concept clear.) Tj
T*
(Students should be able to explain what Programming means, identify where it appears in) Tj
T*
(Computer Science, and describe the main purpose of the topic without relying on) Tj
T*
(memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Programming is algorithms, logic, sequence, selection, and) Tj
T*
(repetition. This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the) Tj
T*
(idea actually works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or) Tj
T*
(patterns behind Programming and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In Computer) Tj
T*
(Science, success usually depends on understanding the commands, structure, and logic) Tj
T*
(that belong to the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Programming is to connect the explanation directly to writing a) Tj
T*
(simple program that makes decisions. That kind of system or code example shows students) Tj
T*
(how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner should be able to) Tj
T*
(state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the question, and then apply) Tj
T*
(the logical procedure with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Why Errors Happen) Tj
T*
