(One common difficulty in Programming is coding without first planning the logic. This) Tj
T*
(matters because many learners can repeat a definition but still fail to use it) Tj
T*
(correctly. A real textbook lesson should therefore point out not only the correct) Tj
T*
(method, but also the exact place where students often go wrong. Learning improves when) Tj
T*
(the student compares correct reasoning with incorrect reasoning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect basic algorithm and control-structure questions. The most effective) Tj
T*
(habit is to read the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then) Tj
T*
(attempt a similar question alone. This turns Programming into something the student can) Tj
T*
(genuinely study and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Programming should first be understood as a computing concept before it is treated as) Tj
T*
(an exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand algorithms, logic, sequence, selection, and repetition) Tj
T*
(because it controls how questions in Programming are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Programming uses the correct logical procedure and explains why) Tj
T*
(that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Writing a simple program that makes decisions is the type of application that helps) Tj
T*
(move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Programming.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind algorithms, logic, sequence,) Tj
T*
(selection, and repetition.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct logical procedure step by step instead of jumping to the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on writing a simple program that makes decisions.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in algorithms, logic, sequence, selection, and repetition) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Programming step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on basic algorithm and control-structure) Tj
T*
(questions.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
